<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1774,2015]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,285,1811,1836]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Colour.</emphasis>
Head and body uniformly brown to dark gray above and white below. A dark blotch at base of pectoral fin and caudal fin with dark outer margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1774,2015]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,519,1883,1908]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Geographical distribution.</emphasis>
Indo-West Pacific (except Hawaii) to 
<collectingCountry box="[979,1092,1883,1907]" name="Indonesia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
; north to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1320,1384,1884,1907]" name="Japan" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Japan</collectingCountry>
and Indian Ocean. (
<bibRefCitation author="Mohsin" box="[322,621,1919,1943]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refString="Mohsin, A. K. M &amp; Ambak, M. N. (1996) Marine fishes and fisheries of Malaysia and neighbouring countries. University Pertanian Malaysia Press, Serdang; pp- 743." type="book chapter" year="1996">
Mohsin and Ambak, 
<number box="[561,621,1919,1943]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
